%section.home-importance
  .section-content
    %h2.home-heading--large.home-importance-heading.section-title
      Your business depends on proactive security

    .clearfix
      %article.home-importance-item
        .home-importance-text
          %p.home-heading--small Protect Your Applications
          %p
            Don't leave it to production to find any compromising secrets
            committed in your code

      %article.home-importance-item
        .home-importance-text
          %p.home-heading--small Protect Your Company
          %p
            Security breaches can be enormously expensive, an ounce of
            prevention is worth a pound of cure

      %article.home-importance-item
        .home-importance-text
          %p.home-heading--small Protect Your Customers
          %p
            Ensure the trust you have built with your customers is not eroded
            by a small accident in the development process

%section.value
  .section-content
    %article.value-section
      .value-text
        %h2.home-heading--large
          How it works.
        %p
          Keycomb integrates with your existing workflow by reviewing
          code the moment a GitHub pull request is opened or updated.
          A commit status update will let you know if your code is good to go
          or if there is cause for concern.

      /= image_tag "home-page/hound_flow.png", class: "value-image"

%section.configuration
  .section-content
    .configuration-text
      %h2.home-heading--small
        Service Providers
      %p
        Keycomb is currently scanning for secrets from service providers such as AWS,
        Heroku, GitHub and adding more everyday!
    .configuration-text
      %h2.home-heading--small
        Cyptosystems & Protocols
      %p
        Keycomb searches for secret artifacts of cryptography methods such as RSA,
        PGP, OPENSSH and many others.

%section.home-pricing
  .section-content#pricing
    .section-title
      %h2.home-pricing-heading.home-heading--large
        Pricing.

    %article.plans
      .clearfix
        %h3.plan-category
          Private Repos

        = render(partial: @home.private_plans, as: :plan)

        %h3.plan-category.open-source
          Open Source

        = render(partial: @home.open_source_plans, as: :plan)

